reviews.text:
星期六午餐 特選刺身定食 ($280) 頂呱呱👍👍👍
(牡丹蝦超新鮮、海膽甘甜、中拖羅入口即溶、魷魚夠鮮味、 油甘魚亦很新鮮、鯛魚有口咬口)
小店開業兩年多，有38個座位， 兩位日本廚師主理，店員友善。
附近有兩桌日本人妻子+外籍丈夫+ 混血兒女兒。
連日本人都來的小店， 應該是很不錯吧！
環境不太迫，清靜，食物質素唔錯

香港で本格的な日本料理が堪能できる店です。店員さんも日本語が通じるので安心して注文出来ます。素材・調理ともに本当の日本を味わえる。その日のオススメメニューもあり、サービスレベルも高いです。日本でもなかなかないメニューもあります。特に魚の鮮度が良く他の日本食レストランとは比べ物にならないです。マスターが日本人なので鮮度・品質の管理は抜群だと思います。店内も汚れた箇所はなく本当に日本の店と変わらないので安心して料理が食べられます。ここが他の日本食レストランとの差だと思います。
日本人としてオススメ出来る店だと思います。
Good old Japanese. Authentic and great quality since I know them. Sushi, hot and cold dishes top notch
Run by Japanese chef. Everything was delicious. Not cheap but worth every penny.

reviews.text: imo it's one of the best tempura you can get in hong kong and the standard is high even when compared with those in Japan. Flattered by their dinner a la carte menu and would love to visit again for their high quality food and service.

Not the best smelling entrance but Basic, hearty value for money tempura specialist.   Part of the Sushi Hiro group. Good set meals comprising tempura, sashimi and eel rice.  Crowded, run down, fast table turnover restaurant

A great bargain for high end ingredients in tempura, if you come here for lunch. 16 pieces that you can pick from a menu for 430 Hong Kong dollars. If you pick the right ones, they would have cost you over a thousand dollars at a la carte prices. But of course most people will order sets too at dinner. But no where near the bargain lunch prices can be.
You can order equally nice set lunches at 240 Hong Kong dollars. I go for the tempura shrimp cake on rice, raw tuna on rice, and fish head soup.
If you do lunch you have to know two things. They use sesams oil from Japan for two meals only. Dinner and then lunch the next day. So the trade off for the lunch bargain price is the second meal of the oil. Which brings us to the second point. Go as early as you can, and try to be the first guests to arrive. Then the oil is as fresh as dinner time. When the lunch traffic builds up the cooking gets sloppy too.
Do reserve for lunch.

Ten Yoshi, 9/F Henry House

Taste like if you are in Japan!
Excellent tempura and sushi restaurant.
Only six tables and a bar table at restaurant.
Table booking is recommended!
Best tempura ever! More than just prawns and veggies, there are really unique fresh fish options.
